This presidential memorandum, issued on May 12, 2020, delegates functions and authorities under Section 1260J of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2020 to the Secretary of Commerce, in consultation with the Attorney General. The memorandum states that this delegation applies to any future public law provision that is the same or substantially the same as the referenced provision. The Secretary of Commerce is also authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by President Donald J. Trump.